    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv Thanks for responding. Here is some code on codesandbox:\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/wizardly-jackson-ovx2f?fontsize=14\r\n\r\nNot sure what you mean about mounting a widget. The hits widget should be enough right?\r\n\r\nYou'll see in the sample that there are results produced but they don't have the query or Designer refinement applied. Have tried various options but none are making a difference. Have tried just the query and not the refinementList, and vice versa. Not 100% sure if initialUiState is meant to have a property of \"indexName\" or \"products\" (which is the actual index name). Have tried both in any case. Have also tried not including this node, i.e. just:\r\n`        initialUiState: {\r\n          refinementList: {\r\n            Designer: [\"Zimmermann\"]\r\n          }\r\n        }`\r\nwhich is how the code example says its done on this page: https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/upgrade-guides/js/#upgrade-from-v3-to-v4\r\n\r\nI'm not the most advanced coder but the documentation in this area seems to be very light.\r\n\r\nShouldn't be any issue on the index side, as falling back to v3 and specifying searchParameters produces expected results. E.g.\r\n`\r\nsearchParameters: {\r\ndisjunctiveFacetsRefinements: {\"Designer\":[\"Zimmermann\"]}\r\n}\r\n`\r\n\r\nAny ideas?",
