  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "```js\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  indexName: \"products\",\r\n  searchClient,\r\n  initialUiState: {\r\n    products: {\r\n      query: \"fakequerythatshouldreturnnoresults\",\r\n      refinementList: {\r\n        Designer: [\"Zimmermann\"]\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n\r\nconst virtualRefinementList = instantsearch.connectors.connectRefinementList(\r\n  () => null\r\n);\r\nconst virtualSearchBox = instantsearch.connectors.connectSearchBox(\r\n  () => null\r\n);\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidgets([\r\n  virtualSearchBox(),\r\n  virtualRefinementList({ attribute: \"Designer\" }),\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n    container: \"#hits\",\r\n    templates: {\r\n      item: `<div>{{Designer}} - {{ProductTitle}}</div>`\r\n    }\r\n  })\r\n]);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is what's meant with \"virtual widget\". \r\n\r\nThanks for pointing out that [this section](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/upgrade-guides/js/#searchparameters) is indeed insufficient to follow if  you didn't already  use advanced InstantSearch features.\r\n\r\nAnother option is the following:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidgets([\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.configure(\r\n      { disjunctiveFacetsRefinements: {\"Designer\":[\"Zimmermann\"]} }\r\n  ),\r\n]);\r\n```",
